name: FDS-SMV bundles prior to 6.3.0
body: On 31 March 2021 we migrated old bundles from Bintray to GitHub.  Note that the source code associated with this Git tag (zip file at the bottom of the asset list) is unrelated to any of the bundles.  To compile source for a specific bundle, first [find the Git hash](https://github.com/firemodels/fds/wiki/SVN-to-Git-hash) for the release and checkout that commit from your cloned repository (see [Git Notes Getting Started](https://github.com/firemodels/fds/wiki/Git-Notes-Getting-Started)). (Yes, it is very complicated; sorry.)

name: FDS 6.6.0 SMV 6.6.0 - FDS6.6.0-131-g88ae75a
body: Note: There was a minor mistake made in tagging this release in that the FDS6.6.0 tag was created before the version string was changed.  The result of this is that if you compile the code from the tar.gz attached to this tag you will see FDS6.5.3 as a version.  It would be problematic to go back and correct this issue at this point.  The issue was fixed prior to compiling the bundle.
